Edwin Sodi of Blackhead Consultancy will continue his evidence on the Asbestos Project in the Free State provincial government. This is a continuation of the Commission's focus on allegations of vast maladministration, fraud and corruption in that province. JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry resumes on Wednesday. The Zondo Commission will continue to hear evidence relating to an asbestos project in the Free State provincial government. Edwin Sodi, the director of Blackhead, is expected to testify. READ: State capture inquiry: Sub-contractor justifies R21m pay day Earlier this month, a sub-contractor testified that he deserves the more than R20-million he pocketed. The state capture inquiry is probing an asbestos contract worth R255-million by the Free State government.